short_desc: Provides supplemental food vouchers, nutritional education and counseling to pregnant and lactating women and children age 5 or under who are at nutritional or medical risk. Also serves foster parents with children under 5
description: WIC is a federally-funded health and nutrition program for women, infants, and children. Helps families by providing checks for buying healthy supplemental foods from WIC-authorized vendors, nutrition education, breastfeeding support, and help finding healthcare and other community services.
